---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import claimsData from '../data/claims.json';
import toolsData from '../data/tools.json';

const title = 'About GEOoptimised: an independent evidence base for AI search';
const description = 'GEOoptimised grades every published claim about AI search by whether it traces to a primary source and reproduces, and publishes exactly what each tool it reviews pays it. Written by Sunny Patel.';

const nonPayers = toolsData.tools.filter(t => !t.affiliate.hasProgram).length;

const schema = [
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
    itemListElement: [
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://geooptimised.com/' },
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'About', item: 'https://geooptimised.com/about/' },
    ],
  },
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'Organization',
    '@id': 'https://geooptimised.com/#organization',
    name: 'GEOoptimised',
    url: 'https://geooptimised.com',
    mainEntityOfPage: 'https://geooptimised.com/about/',
    description: 'An independent evidence base for AI search visibility that grades every published claim by whether it traces to a primary source and reproduces, and publishes exactly what each tool it reviews pays it.',
    disambiguatingDescription: 'GEOoptimised covers generative engine optimisation, meaning how brands come to be cited by AI assistants such as ChatGPT, Perplexity, Claude and Google AI Overviews. It is unrelated to geographic, location-based or geo-targeted marketing.',
    founder: { '@id': 'https://geooptimised.com/#sunny-patel' },
    knowsAbout: [
      'Generative engine optimisation',
      'Answer engine optimisation',
      'AI search citation behaviour',
      'Evidence grading of marketing claims',
      'AI visibility measurement and its limits',
    ],
  },
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'Person',
    '@id': 'https://geooptimised.com/#sunny-patel',
    name: 'Sunny Patel',
    jobTitle: 'SEO consultant',
    description: 'SEO consultant based in Berkshire, England. Runs a portfolio of independent websites and publishes what the data shows, including when it contradicts him.',
    address: { '@type': 'PostalAddress', addressRegion: 'Berkshire', addressCountry: 'GB' },
  },
];
---
<Base title={title} description={description} schema={schema}>
  <section class="wrap pt-14 pb-8">
    <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="data text-[0.7rem] uppercase tracking-widest mb-6" style="color: var(--muted);">
      <a href="/">Home</a> <span aria-hidden="true">/</span> <span style="color: var(--text);">About</span>
    </nav>
    <h1 class="font-serif font-bold text-[2.2rem] sm:text-[2.9rem] leading-[1.08] max-w-[20ch]">About GEOoptimised</h1>
  </section>

  <!-- Entity home. The definitional sentence sits alone, so an LLM can lift it whole. -->
  <section class="wrap pb-12">
    <div class="border-l-4 pl-6 py-1 max-w-[66ch]" style="border-color: var(--text);">
      <p class="font-serif text-[1.32rem] leading-snug" style="color: var(--text);">
        GEOoptimised is an independent evidence base for AI search visibility that grades every published claim by
        whether it traces to a primary source and reproduces, and that publishes exactly what each tool it reviews
        pays it.
      </p>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-[66ch] text-[0.98rem]" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
      GEOoptimised covers <strong style="color: var(--text);">generative engine optimisation</strong>, meaning how
      brands come to be cited by AI assistants such as ChatGPT, Perplexity, Claude and Google AI Overviews. It is
      unrelated to geographic, location-based or geo-targeted marketing, which shares the abbreviation and none of
      the subject matter.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="prose-wrap pb-24 copy">
    <h2>Why this exists</h2>
    <p>
      In July 2026 we set out to check the statistics that writing about AI search repeats most often. Of the claims
      we examined, three led to no primary source we could locate at all. One cited a source whose numbers we could
      not surface from the page. The single most-quoted figure in the entire field, the
      <a class="link" href="/the-40-percent-claim/">40% visibility uplift</a>, turned out to describe a research
      benchmark and is routinely presented as a measurement of ChatGPT.
    </p>
    <p>
      Then we found something worse. A genuinely rigorous statistic, from SparkToro, had drifted by a factor of ten
      as it was retold, and we had already repeated the wrong version in our own notes before we checked. Nobody had
      lied. Somebody had paraphrased, and then somebody had paraphrased the paraphrase.
    </p>
    <p>
      Every serious dataset in this field belongs to a company selling something: Ahrefs, Semrush, Profound, Peec.
      Their research is often excellent. Nobody independent was checking whether the numbers survived contact with
      their own sources, and nobody was disclosing what they earned from the tools they recommended. Those are two
      small jobs. They do not require anyone's funding. So we did them.
    </p>

    <h2>What we publish</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong><a class="link" href="/evidence/">The evidence ledger</a>.</strong> {claimsData.claims.length} claims, each graded on one of six grades, each with its primary source, sample size, publication date, and a note recording whether we personally reproduced the number.</li>
      <li><strong><a class="link" href="/who-pays-us/">Who pays us</a>.</strong> The exact affiliate terms of every tool we review. {nonPayers} of them cannot pay us anything, and they are named alongside the ones that can.</li>
      <li><strong><a class="link" href="/corrections/">Corrections</a>.</strong> Permanent and dated. The first two entries are our own errors, made before this site had a single reader.</li>
      <li><strong><a class="link" href="/methodology/">The method</a>.</strong> Published in full, so you can audit a grade rather than trust it.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What we do not do</h2>
    <p>
      We do not sell GEO services, and there is nothing here to book. We do not sell a tool, so we have no dashboard
      to defend. We run no display advertising and will not, because an ad network would choose what appears beside
      our grading. We do not accept sponsored placements or paid reviews. We intend to earn affiliate commission,
      and when we do, the tool's row will say so on the same day.
    </p>

    <h2>Who writes it</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Sunny Patel</strong> is an SEO consultant based in Berkshire, England. He runs a portfolio of
      independent websites and publishes what the data shows, including when it contradicts him. GEOoptimised exists
      because he could not verify the numbers he kept being asked to repeat.
    </p>
    <p>
      No claim is made here about certifications, awards, employers or clients. The community this site is written
      for treats the anonymous "GEO expert" as the villain of the story, and it is right to. A named author who can
      be held to what he published is the minimum, not a credential.
    </p>

    <h2>How to hold us to this</h2>
    <p>
      Pick any claim in the ledger. Follow its primary source. Read what it actually measured. If our grade is wrong,
      <a class="link" href="/contact/">send us the source</a> and we will regrade it in public, on the corrections
      page, with the date and what changed. We do not silently edit pages.
    </p>
    <p>
      That offer is the entire business model of a site like this. If we ever quietly fix something instead of
      logging it, we have nothing left to sell.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
